From: Performance Patch Series
Subject: [PATCH 01/10] Fix PatternToRegEx to escape regex metacharacters

Bottleneck #7: PatternToRegEx replaces _ with . and % with .* but does
not escape other regex metacharacters in the input. This means inputs
containing characters like (, ), [, ], +, *, ?, {, }, ^, $, |, or \
produce incorrect regex patterns or throw exceptions.

The fix escapes the input first with Regex.Escape(), then replaces the
SQL LIKE wildcards (now escaped as \_ and \%) with their regex equivalents.

---
 csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs | 7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs b/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs
index bfc6fa5..abeef1a 100644
--- a/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs
+++ b/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs
@@ -1242,8 +1242,13 @@ namespace AdbcDrivers.BigQuery
             if (pattern == null)
                 return ".*";
 
+            // Escape regex metacharacters first (e.g. . * + ? become \. \* \+ \?),
+            // then convert SQL LIKE wildcards to regex equivalents.
+            // Regex.Escape does NOT escape _ or % (they aren't regex metacharacters),
+            // so we replace them directly after escaping everything else.
+            string escaped = Regex.Escape(pattern);
             StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder("(?i)^");
-            string convertedPattern = pattern.Replace("_", ".").Replace("%", ".*");
+            string convertedPattern = escaped.Replace("_", ".").Replace("%", ".*");
             builder.Append(convertedPattern);
             builder.Append("$");
 
